amplayd (0.1.5-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * If the device does not exist, retry instead of giving up. If the device
    does not exist on startup, the daemon waits and tries to open it every few
    seconds. If the device disappears during operation, it should now be
    reopened.
  * Corrects a bunch of errors in the playlist management.

 -- Hermann Schwarting <debian@knackich.de>  Sat, 21 Apr 2007 23:57:29 +0200

